title: Grateful Dead Live at Boston Garden on 1991-09-20
lineage: 16 bit – 48kHz DAT Master > TASCAM DA-20 (SPDIF out) -> LynxTWO-B Audio Reference Interface (SPDIF in) -> Wavelab 6.0 (Weiss Saracon for 16 BIT – 44.1kHz SRC and POWR-3 Dither)
taper: James Young and Clay Brennecke and Dan Oneil
description:
Set 1

Touch Of Grey, Little Red Rooster, Jack A Roe, Black Throated Wind, Stagger Lee, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song

Set 2

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Fire On The Mountain, Estimated Prophet-> Truckin'-> Jam-> Drums-> Jam-> All Along The Watchtower-> Morning Dew, E: Turn On Your Love Light

reviews.review_text:
good w/eq VG show.

w/eq, a VG recording (both sets).

Warning: during Birdsong there's an out-of-control yeller/whistler who fairly quickly is subdued, but a part of the song is ruined.

tha GARDEN So it goes FOB at one of the rowdiest venues on the tour, I'm amazed the crowd is behaved on the recording. So many of the east coast FOB recordings have screamers, drunks, trippers. Other than BS, this is really clean. Just listen to the roof blow off the joint when Jer starts the Fire. You'll never get the excitement of the room from the SDB. Great recording, thanks to all for making this one available!

A quality audience recording Surveyed a lot of Help on the way's here. I wanted one where Garcia got all the words without a single flub, and one followed by a perfectly played intro section into Slipnot. There actually are'nt a lot of versions that get all the words right in addition to getting all the complexities of that instrumental section with no mistakes. Some have either/or, and many have neither. Never thought I'd find it in a 1991 version, this is very strong performance....and followed by fire instead of Franklin's! Definite DL. Thanks for the excellent work.

Beautiful stylings and rhythm courtesy Bruce H Agree with earlier review, I'd just like to add that Brucce Hornsby's powerful, pretty presence is divine, he with Jerry made me cry on Morning Dew.  What a sweetheart!

Crowd does sound like a winning Game 7 at the World Series against you know who, I'm sure the boys were a bit stunned, even with all they've seen it had to be quite the show for them as well..

This one is all good.
